        "text": "Neuroscientific research has shown that this feedback loop is essential for normal brain development in children (Denes 2016). There are windows in the maturation process of a developing child wherein interaction with the environment must take place for normal brain development to progress. Once the window closes, brain plasticity reduces and full competence is not achieved."
